	url = {https://www.jstor.org/stable/25050821},
	abstract = {In this paper we show how to represent the least squares regression estimators as a ratio of U-statistics. In fact, using this representation we define a more general class of linear regression estimators that include the least squares estimators as a special case. This representation allows us to use well-known results of properties of U-statistics to establish properties of the linear regression estimators. In particular, we establish Berry-Esseen type bounds on the rate of convergence of the distribution of the standardized estimators to a normal distribution. Assuming stationarity of the regressor and disturbance terms, we establish bounds when these terms are either independent or satisfy a weak dependency condition.},
